prices do not necessarily indicate a scam. in a teahouse, ¥50-200 per cup or pot of tea is common. tea samplings may also be expensive. in a bar, price range is even bigger, in which ¥10-80 per bottle of beer is a norm and having a new bottle of wine can cost from a few hundred to many thousands. however, in all genuine places, prices should be stated clearly on a menu. finally, although it is perfectly possible to pay more than rmb1000 in a high-end teahouse and bar, run-of-the-mill teas and bars should not be nearly this expensive. such 